[SN]TITLE[SN]
FTSE 100 little changed on Friday

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
(Close): London's FTSE 100 was little changed on Friday, as gains by the likes of Easyjet and Marks and Spencer outweighed falls in mining firms.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The FTSE 100 closed higher by 1 point at 6,916.
Budget airline Easyjet and Marks and Spencer both closed up more then 3%, while shares in the miners Antofagasta and Rio Tinto led the losers.
Bottling firm Coca-Cola HBC rose another 2% after Thursday's 7% lift following better than expected results.
